xim-wayland
===========

xim-wayland is a protocol translator between XIM and wl_text_input
protocol.  The code is self-contained, including an XCB binding of XIM
server protocol, and doesn't require any extra library except
libwayland-client and libxcb.

Usage
=====

Under weston session with XWayland enabled, do:

$ ./xim-wayland --locale=en &
$ LANG=en_US.utf8 XMODIFIERS=@im=wayland xterm
